    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-09-17T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-09-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="209"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                <head>209. Record of Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d209fn1">Source:
                        National Archives and Records Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1"
                            >RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66, <gloss target="#t_POL1"
                            >POL</gloss> 27 INDIA–<gloss target="#t_Pak1">PAK</gloss>. Secret;
                        Sensitive; <gloss target="#t_Exdis1">Exdis</gloss>. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SJJ1">Sisco</persName> in <gloss target="#t_IO1"
                        >IO</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-09-17T18:00:00-04:00">September 17, 1965, 6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">UNCLEARED SUMMARY OF WHITE HOUSE MEETING ON SOUTH ASIAN
                    PROBLEMS</p>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>The President</item>
                    <item>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Under Secretary <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">Ball</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RVAWFJ1">Raborn</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_TLE1">Thompson</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Assistant Secretary <persName corresp="#p_SJJ1">Sisco</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">McGeorge Bundy</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The President decided the following on the Indian-Pakistan situation: <list>
                        <label>1)</label>
                        <item>We would continue to give the strongest support to the Secretary
                            General and the Security Council. He approved the current draft of the
                                resolution.<note n="2" xml:id="d209fn2">Apparent reference to a
                                draft of the resolution adopted by the Security Council on September
                                20 which demanded that a cease-fire between India and Pakistan take
                                effect on September 22. (<gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> doc.
                                S/RES/211)</note> In general we are to emphasize publicly the
                            efforts that we are making through the <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                            here at the Department and in New York.</item>
                        <label>2)</label>
                        <item>No messages would go from the President to Ayub and <persName
                                corresp="#p_SLB1">Shastri</persName> for the time being. This might
                            be reviewed in light of whatever Security Council action is
                            taken.</item>
                        <label>3)</label>
                        <item>Both Defense and State should develop contingency plans on possible
                            next steps for the President’s review.</item>
                        <label>4)</label>
                        <item>No preparatory military moves should now be made in the area.</item>
                        <label>5)</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">George Ball</persName> is to prepare a
                            memorandum giving the pros and cons on whether we should cut off food
                            supplies.</item>
                        <label>6)</label>
                        <item>
                            <p>[<hi rend="italic">8 lines of source text not declassified</hi>]</p>
                            <p>With respect to the three questions the Indians have put to us<note
                                    n="3" xml:id="d209fn3">See <ref target="#d208">Document
                                        208</ref>.</note> and which have now become public
                                knowledge, <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">George Ball</persName> will
                                brief Greenfield on the following line: That the Indians have
                                discussed with us their concern over the <gloss target="#t_ChiCom1"
                                    >Chicom</gloss> development; we have discussed with them our
                                concern in this regard; and that we will take note of these as we
                                pursue our policy within the Security Council.</p>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
